{"HEIGH-HO":[{"def":"An exclamation of surprise, joy, dejection, uneasiness, weariness, etc.","pos":""}],"HEIGHT":[{"def":"The condition of being high; elevated position.","pos":""},{"def":"The distance to which anything rises above its foot, above that on which in stands, above the earth, or above the level of the sea; altitude; the measure upward from a surface, as the floor or the ground, of animal, especially of a man; stature.","pos":""}],"HEIGHTEN":[{"def":"To make high; to raise higher; to elevate.","pos":""},{"def":"To carry forward; to advance; to increase; to augment; to aggravate; to intensify; to render more conspicuous; -- used of things, good or bad; as, to heighten beauty; to heighten a flavor or a tint.","pos":""}],"HEIGHTENER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, heightens.","pos":""}],"HEINOUS":[{"def":"Hateful; hatefully bad; flagrant; odious; atrocious; giving great great offense; -- applied to deeds or to character.","pos":""}],"HEIR":[{"def":"One who inherits, or is entitled to succeed to the possession of, any property after the death of its owner; one on whom the law bestows the title or property of another at the death of the latter.","pos":""},{"def":"One who receives any endowment from an ancestor or relation; as, the heir of one's reputation or virtues.","pos":""}],"HEIRDOM":[{"def":"The state of an heir; succession by inheritance.","pos":""}],"HEIRESS":[{"def":", A female heir.","pos":""}],"HEIRLESS":[{"def":"Destitute of an heir.","pos":""}],"HEIRLOOM":[{"def":"Any furniture, movable, or personal chattel, which by law or special custom descends to the heir along with the inheritance; any piece of personal property that has been in a family for several generations.","pos":""}],"HEIRSHIP":[{"def":"The state, character, or privileges of an heir; right of inheriting.","pos":""}]}